				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				<DIV>I'm now getting reports filtering in (yeah, I keep my ears open <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> ) that the quest we've been working on is <EM>intented </EM>to open the way to Broodlands, but it appears broken on E'ci. The quest is given by Xoramin Sprysprocket and sends to on various subquests. When someone completes it, Mecha-Miner spawns and starts trying to chip away at the rocks blocking Broodlands.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>From what I'm told, this is supposed to happen once per server, and once he expldoes, the way is open to all. I can confirm that on E'ci, several people have completed this step and gotten the reward, and the rocks are still blocking the way. I'm not 100% sure it's a bug... but as I said, we've learned that people&nbsp;quickly get frustrated with limited zone access. While I'm sure it'll open up soon - I had so much fun in beta, I wanted to play around in new places today! <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
				
